    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device with medium model influence and high decision consequence. Mesh convergence GCI of 1.9% exceeds requirements. NIH prediction error of 8.3% mean relative error is within the 15% acceptance criterion. RH < 1 confirmed at all 5 operating points. The computational model is deemed credible for the intended use of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions to support 510(k) submission.",
